{
  "stem": "13584.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It's a port city of the Caspian Sea.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I remember this, the sleeping on the streets.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we were not the only one.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "There was a whole long row of-- of people, called bezhenets, means refugees, waiting for, apparently, a barge.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I remember we boarded a barge.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "A lot of people were on a barge to cross the Caspian Sea on the other side to the Asian part.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And when we crossed on the Asian part, this I remember.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I don't know how it happened, but apparently those refugees had transportation.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "The transportation were on oxen.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Oxen and wagons were provided for for these refugees I don't know how.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And we were all loaded on these wagons.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And we went through, I remember, days and days-- and the heat was terrible-- through a-- through a-- oh, gosh-- through Karakum, through the-- you know, through the-- the wilderness of Karakum.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "There were-- we did not have water.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "We met there nomads, still nomads, Turkish descent.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "They tried to help us.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "About 12 or 15 days we were traveling this-- this way, until we reached-- we reached another kolkhoz, already in Asia, in Kazakhstan-- in Kazakhstan, where my mother worked in field by potatoes, collect potatoes, worked on picking out potatoes.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "In this-- in this village, we did not live in a house.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "We lived in a-- well, in a bunker in the earth.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "It was-- I cannot say it right.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "It was inside.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "You had to go down to the earth a little.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "The hole was covered with a little roof.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And that's where we lived with another family, with another Jewish family.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "The other Jewish family was from Odessa, I recall.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And my mother used to go and work and evening used to come.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
